ter-selected starbursts with similar far-IR luminosities\nsuggest that the dominant star formation in ULIRGs at moderate redshifts takes\nplace on smaller spatial scales than at higher redshifts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 18 Feb 2007 20:32:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-02-11"}
