 hybrid can undercover severely when taken to high Z\nvalues. We also examine the profile likelihood method, which has long been used\nin GRA and HEP; it provides an excellent approximation in much of the parameter\nspace, as previously studied by Rolke and collaborators.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Feb 2007 09:44:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 7 Jun 2008 15:30:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 23 Aug 2008 18:57:12 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 20 Nov 2008 20:48:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-20"}
